speech.p:
(a) for paragraph 1 of Schedule 1 to the said Act of 1939, as amended, there shall be substituted the following paragraph;
'(1) The annual amount of any periodical payment made to any person by virtue of his past membership of the House of Commons shall not exceed £2,016 or such sum as, in the opinion of the trustees, will bring his income up to £3,730 per annum whichever is the less:
Provided that if, having regard to length of service and need, the trustees think fit, they may make a larger payment not exceeding £3,894 or such sum as, in their opinion, will bring his income up to £5,608 per annum, whichever is the less.'
